; Downstream-differential negate fixture (checkpoint (d), analysis sec 4.5
; R9). A MONOTONE-negated negate (seen has no @never, feed/unsee are
; non-differential, so only the `-` crossover arm exists) whose OUTPUT feeds
; a FURTHER differential rule one stratum down:
;
;   copy(A, B) : feed(A, B).
;   seen(A)    : unsee(A).
;   out(A, B)  : copy(A, B), !seen(A).       monotone-negated negate
;   flag(A, B) : out(A, B), active(A).       downstream differential join
;
; `active` is @differential, so flag's stratum consumes out's net_additions
; frontier at seed time. This discriminates the R3 seed-before-drain
; ordering: a crossover fold emitted AFTER the claim drains could let a
; phantom `+` be claimed on `out` and leak a spurious NetAdded frontier
; entry, which the downstream flag rule would DOUBLE-COUNT (out(A,B) already
; present but re-emitted). The observable is flag's membership: it must
; track out x active exactly, with no double-count survivors.
#message feed(u64 A, u64 B).
#message unsee(u64 A).
#message active(u64 A) @differential.

#local copy(u64 A, u64 B).
#local seen(u64 A).
#local out(u64 A, u64 B).

#query flag_out(free u64 A, free u64 B).

copy(A, B) : feed(A, B).
seen(A) : unsee(A).
out(A, B) : copy(A, B), !seen(A).
flag_out(A, B) : out(A, B), active(A).
